## Decisions Made
- Guard conditions (non-Report-PR branch, bot comment) should result in skip/success, not failure — failure status should be reserved for genuine errors

## Problems Encountered
- curate-report workflow showed failure for expected guard conditions: bot comment rejection by claude-code-action, and branch prefix mismatch
- Two separate failure modes required two different fix approaches: job-level `if` for bot filter, step-level output flag for branch check

## Constraints Identified
- GitHub Actions `issue_comment` event fires on all comments — cannot filter at event level, must handle in job/step conditions
- `claude-code-action` internally rejects bot actors — must prevent bot comments from reaching the action at all

## Open Questions
- None

## Context
Fixed curate-report.yml to properly distinguish expected guard conditions (skip) from real errors (failure). Bot comments now filtered at job-level `if`, and non-Report-PR branch validation uses a skip output flag instead of `core.setFailed()`.
